The paper deals with the reconstruction of medical images using a combination of variational models and deep learning. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of variational models also suggests a connection to optimization and information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper deals with medical imaging (cs.MM) and involves the use of neural networks (cs.AI).
